# ── Build-context hygiene ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Everything listed here is NEVER sent to the Docker daemon. Two reasons:
# 1. Speed: the context is tar'd and uploaded before the build starts —
#    node_modules + the SQLite DB would add ~1GB per build.
# 2. Security: files in the context can end up baked into image layers,
#    where anyone with the image can extract them (docker save + untar).
#    Runtime state and secrets must NEVER be part of an image.

# VCS + editor
.git
.gitignore
.claude
*.md
!README.md

# Runtime state (DB, logs, breakers, backups) — lives in a VOLUME, not the image
backend/data

# Local virtualenvs / caches — rebuilt inside the image from uv.lock
backend/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache

# Frontend: node_modules is restored by `npm ci` in the build stage;
# dist is BUILT in the build stage (never trust a possibly-stale local dist)
frontend/node_modules
frontend/dist

# Tests are not shipped in the runtime image (smaller attack surface).
# CI runs them from the repo checkout, not from the image.
backend/tests

# Secrets — belt & suspenders (they're gitignored too, but the docker
# context is built from the working tree, not from git)
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Infra/docs not needed inside the app image
docs
scripts
infra
justfile
